      • btnSpecialInstructionEdit1OnAction

        protected void btnSpecialInstructionEdit1OnAction​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        btnSpecialInstructionEdit1OnAction first asks the user whether they want to edit the TextArea, and if so, changes the txtSpecialInstruction1 TextArea to editable, the "Edit" button to "Save", and disables all other modifiable (or used to modify) controls while the editing is in progress. Once the user clicks on "Save", the new contents of the TextArea will be pushed to the database, the disabled controls will be re-enabled, and the button text will revert back to "Edit", along with changing the TextArea back to non-editable.
        Parameters:
        event - The ActionEvent that is passed to this event handler. (Requirement 5.2.1, 5.2.1.1, 5.2.1.2, 5.2.1.3)

      • editConfirmationMessage

        private boolean editConfirmationMessage​(javafx.scene.control.Button btnName,
                                        java.lang.String name,
                                        java.lang.String editSave)
        editConfirmationMessage displays the confirmation message when the user clicks an "Edit" or "Save" Button on the form.
        Parameters:
        btnName - A reference to the Button in order to edit its text.
        name - The String name of the button.
        editSave - The resulting String text to set to the button if the user clicks "Yes".
